page.title: 01WARBOYS, CAMBRIDGESHIRE
page.content: In the Domesday Book{Warboys}is spelt "Wardebusc", thought to mean "Look-out-wood".{Warboys }has grown up on the southern edge of the Fens so it is known to be a good farming area, particularly for arable crops. In 1901 much of the west side of {Warboys}was burned down by fire so there are not many buildings that are old and of historic interest. Just outside{Warboys}is an airfield that was used in the Second World War.Now it is mainly used for arable crops and there is a small industrial estate there. The historic parts of{Warboys}are the Clock Tower,Church, and Manor House.{ {Warboys}is situated some seven miles north-east of Huntingdon,four miles south of Ramsey and about seven miles north of St.Ives. The population of {Warboys}for 1985 is 2,870.
